omply with the martyr’s whim and brighten up things for him by granting him the knowledge that in dying he performs a good useful deed—of a crude material nature, perhaps, but anyhow, useful.”

Lydia hugged my leg and stared up at me.

“His plan is as follows,” I went on, in a bland voice: “My life, say, is insured for half a million. In a wood, somewhere, my corpse is found. My widow, that is you—”

“Oh, stop saying such horrors,” cried Lydia, scrambling up from the carpet. 